title: Grateful Dead Live at Silva Hall, Hult Center on 1984-05-08
description:
Set 1

Beer Barrel Polka, Jack Straw, Cold Rain & Snow, Minglewood Blues, Candyman, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain-> Might As Well

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Touch Of Gray-> Women Are Smarter, Terrapin Station-> Drums*-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew, E: Sugar Magnolia, E: Brokedown Palace

*with Ken Kesey and the Thunder Machine

reviews.review_text:
Best LLR of all time, and my favorite 84 tape! Hunter works his magic again with this crispy matrix that puts you right there in the hall with the boys.

Looks Like Rain is my all time favorite version, certainly top 5 performance.  The last 4 or 5 minutes are total fire --- I love how they jam out --- it's so soulful and funky it is literally begging to be covered by a modern day R&B group.  Very sample-able if you dig it.

FWIW, I used to avoid all mid-80s shows because of the keyboard sounds.  Brent's toy piano still isn't my favorite, but the "Plinko-style" keyboard he uses is!  

The Scarlet coda fires on all cylinders, very unique version with a seamless jammy transition into Touch of Grey.

I love this early, fast, chugging version of Touch of Grey.  It's a must hear --- even my 3 year old son was singing along!!

Then the jammy, Plinko-keys heavy version Woman are Smarter is so nice too!  

Getting used to Brent's mid-80s (83, 84, 85) keyboard sounds took some getting used to, but this show is the panacea!

Hult 5-8-84 Ken Kesey introduces...
Super fun shows at the Hult. 
The boys came to play. 
Morning Dew left a mark...
